2. Deterministic vs Stochastic
e When a uniqueness in the agent's current state completely determines
the next state of the agent, the environment is said to be deterministic.
e The stochastic environment is random in nature which is not unique and
cannot be completely determined by the agent.
¢ Examples:
© Chess - there would be only a few possible moves for a chess
piece at the current state and these moves can be determined.
° Self-Driving Cars- the actions of a self-driving car are not
unique, it varies time to time.
